records.addlTxt: Defendant Jeffrey J Bryan in court with attorney David R. Dickmann.  Derek Dominguez appeared for the State of Wisconsin. Atty. Dickmann requests a restitution breakdown from the State.  Court states he may serve his jail time in Clark County but may not have electronic monitoring.  Court order DNA surcharge only on Ct. 1.

Defendant Jeffrey J Bryan in court with attorney David R. Dickmann.  Derek Dominguez appeared for the State of Wisconsin.  Wayne Schultz Jr. is sworn as witness and testifies to being an investigator for the Wood County Sheriff's Department.  Testifies to a tip coming in the the Sheriff's Department on Dec. 26, 2013 regarding the defendant being involved with some burglaries in the area.  Exhibit 1 is reviewed, tip received.  Exhibit 1 is entered into evidence.  The witness testifies to the tip received and the burglaries at the businesses in question.  Testifies to when the owners of the businesses where out of town and when the burglaries happened.  Testifies that information regarding who was burglarized was not made public knowledge.  Tesitifes that the tip mentioning the correct person being burglarized was important.   Testifies to other burglaries in the area and the tip correctly identifying them.  Testifies that a gas station in Hewitt was burglarizes on Jan. 13, 2014, which the tip from Dec. 26, 2013 implied was going to happen.  The witness testifies to videos, shoe imprints and other evidence obtained at the burglarized businesses.  The witness identifies Jeffrey Bryan as the defendant in court, Court accepts.  The witness testifies that the man in the videos and the defendant match. Detective Schultz testifies to speaking with the defendants wife.  Testifies that she said after looking at the videos that it looked like her husband and identified a backback as matching one they had.  Testifies that the burglar entered through the front doors which is unique at the burglarized sites.   Testifies to financial records obtained at 2 casinos in regards to the defendant and his wife.  Testifies to the expenses of the defendant.  Testifies to visiting Jeffrey at his home.  Testifies to what was found at the defendants home that matched things in regards to the burglaries.  11:20, Atty. Dickman cross examines the witness.  Testifies to how he wrote his notes he has today in Court.  Court orders the State to turn over police reports to the defendants attorney.  Court recesses for the State to make copies of the police reports.  11:29, Court reconvenes.  Court addresses the parties and State will provide all reports to Atty. Dickman today and Atty. Dickman continues while copies are being made.    Atty. Dickman reviews how the tip was received by the Wood County Sheriffs Department.  The witness testifies that he believes the Short burglary was kept out of the paper.  The witness testifies to how the shoe implant was identified as being New Balance. Officer Schultz testifies to identifying factors in the videos.  Testifies to the alarm at Pomps and that it was in working order.  Testifies to the gambling loses and gains at the casinos for the defendant and his wife.  Testifies to where Jeffrey said he got the money to gamble. 11:42, redirect from the State.    No witness from the defendants, but Atty. Dickman makes a statement.    Court finds probable cause.  Pre-trial conference scheduled for April 2, 2015 at 09:00 am.
Preliminary hearing and Arraignment on January 8, 2015 at 10:30 am.
